  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  ≥1 CTO lesion amenable to PCI.

          -  Stable and stabilized coronary artery disease

          -  Symptoms (angina pectoris or shortness of breath) and/or signs of reversible perfusion
             defect by SPECT, PET or MR and/or angiographic/echocardiographic indication of
             reversible ischemia.

          -  CTO lesion in a major coronary vessel supplying a significant myocardial territory
             (vessel diameter usually ≥3mm).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Expected survival &lt;1 year.

          -  Renal failure on dialysis.

          -  Stable non-CTO lesions treated within one month.

          -  Declined informed consent.

          -  Regarding CMR: allergy to contrast medium, severe obesity, claustrophobia and certain
             metallic implants
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
